value.value: The proportion, quantity, or volume of the thin, yellow, milky fluid secreted by the mammary gland, before or after parturition, preceding the production of milk.
The proportion or number of somatic cells (leukocytes and epithelial cells) present in colostrum.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of beta-lactoglobulin, which may bind retinol; this milk constituent is allergenic.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of whey acidic protein (WAP), a major protein of whey in rodents and rabbits (as well as marsupials), which belongs to the four disulfide core family.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of lactoferrin, a globular multifunctional protein with antimicrobial activity; part of innate defense.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in colostrum of chemical substances produced by an organ, cells of an organ, or scattered cells, having a specific regulatory effect on the activity of an organ or organs.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in colostrum of members of the hormone family that includes estrogens, progesterone, glucocorticoids, and androgens.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in colostrum of the peptide hormone secreted by white adipocytes and believed to regulate food intake and energy balance.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in colostrum of the hormone that stimulates milk secretion.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in colostrum of any factors which promote cell proliferation.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the location or arrangement of the outer ears in relation to each other or to the skull.

The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of any substance, usually a peptide or steroid, that has a specific metabolic regulatory effect on the activity or behavior of cells expressing a receptor for the hormone.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of members of the hormone family that includes estrogens, progesterone, glucocorticoids, and androgens.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of the peptide hormone secreted by white adipocytes and believed to regulate food intake and energy balance.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of the hormone that stimulates milk secretion.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of any factors which promote cell proliferation.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of casein, the predominant phosphoprotein in milk.

definition.value: accounts for nearly 80% of the protein in cow's milk and cheese

The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of alpa-S2-casein, a minor form of casein.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of kappa-casein, a casein which plays a crucial role in micellar structure; its concentration determines micellar size.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of beta-casein in milk.
The proportion, quantity, or volume of this element in milk.

Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the systematic arrangement of the nerve fibers that convey impulses from the central nervous system to stimulate muscle contraction or glandular secretion.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of lactose, the major sugar found in colostrum and milk; it is composed of one molecule of glucose and one molecule of galactose.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of any inorganic element or compound that has importance in body functions.
The proportion or number of nerve fibers that convey impulses from the central nervous system to stimulate muscle contraction or glandular secretion.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of this metallic bivalent element with atomic symbol Ca and atomic number 20.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of potassium, an alkaline metallic element.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of sodium, a metallic element.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of this nonmetallic essential element which occurs naturally in phosphates and takes part in a broad variety of chemical reactions.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of any binary compound of chlorine.
The proportion, quantity, or volume in milk of  this alkaline earth element, atomic number 12, atomic symbol Mg.
The proportion or number of nerve fibers to sympathetic termini.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the systematic organization of nerve fibers to sympathetic termini.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the physical magnitude of the lower chamber(s) of the heart.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the process of blood vessel formation and remodeling, following initial formation of the vascular network.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the initial establishment of the vascular network.
Any measurable or observable characteristic related to the function of or processes in the hollow, muscular organ that pumps blood through the body.
